content.description: Stand start on good crimps about head height on the face and not any of the broken stuff around the corner. Go up and trend right along the desperately flat-to-sloped corner using funky beta to keep it reasonable. The crux is near the top where it blanks out, so one will need to keep a cool head to slowly work the holds to get one's feet over the top. The fall up there is scary but safe, but it's a bit of a way up there once you commit to the moves.
content.protection: Two pads. One won't cover enough ground, as you go right (or just have the pad for the top part on the right).
content.location: It ascends the main face's left corner - not the broken stuff past it. See the pic.

content.description: Sit Start with both hands on the obvious chunky holds and move left and up.
This is a good warm-up for the area. Stand start on the holds as shown in the picture. Go up and a little to the left, finishing up on the right-ish corner of the main face.
content.location: It is on the right side of the face - not the stuff to the right of the face that is set back from the face that forms the broken right corner. See the pic.

content.description: This is the stand start to Highway Noise. Start with your left hand on the chunky start hold and your right hand is on the lower, triangular pocket. Get delicate feet, and make 3 big moves to the topout.
Sit start on a good, obvious, chunky start hold, and move your way up and to the right using the triangular pockets. Delicate feet and 4 big moves to a solid top out.
content.location: This is on the South Overhang. You can see it from Fellsway West just north of Sheepfold entrance.

content.description: The south end of the outcrop has an obvious, overhung face.
